<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-488-418  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 488 418.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  Sept 1989 v6 n9 p172(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Turning 40. (comparison of 28 medium-capacity hard disks) (buyersguide)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Spencer, Cheryl England.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A guide to 28 40- to 60-Mbyte hard disk drives for the AppleMacintosh is presented.andP;  All of the products include such basicequipment as cables, power cords, terminators, and formattingsoftware.andP;  Internal hard disks are theoretically more reliablethan external ones because they do not require a separate powersupply, but generate excess heat and are easily jolted.andP;  Externalhard disks take up desk space, making physical design a primaryfactor in drive selection.andP;  Some models are packaged withcomprehensive disk-management and backup utilities, while othersonly include bare-bones diagnostic tools and Apple's slow HDBackupprogram.andP;  Other 'extras' offered by some vendors includepartitioning software and long warranties.andP;  The JasmineTechnologies and La Cie products are recommended for theirexcellent documentation, well-thought-out design, and relativelylow prices.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (equipment and supplies).andO;Topic:     Hardware SelectionHard DiskDirectoriesPerformance Measurement.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographtablegraph.andO;Caption:   Finding a hard disk. (table)Speed tests. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>